The paper proposes a new method for Non-negative matrix factorization (NMF) that is robust to outliers, and evaluates it on image clustering tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also includes theoretical analysis of the proposed method, which could place it in the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
